				</table>

				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Sep 19, 2004 11:12 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 20409<br /><b>Location:</b> NE Indiana, USA (NTSC)
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I recently added compression improvements that saved about 10 KiB:<br /><br /><ul><li>5.2 KiB by compressing help text with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byte_pair_encoding" class="postlink">digram tree encoding (DTE)</a>, the same text codec I used for <a href="https://github.com/pinobatch/rfk-nes" class="postlink">my robotfindskitten port</a></li><li>4.8 KiB by generating the Linearity with grid from Linearity without a grid instead of storing both</li></ul><br />This let me splurge a bit, adding more detail and color to the character on the help screens to match the GBC and GBA versions.</div>

					
						<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table class="tablebg" width="100%" cellspacing="1">
						<tr>
							<td class="row3"><b class="genmed">Attachments: </b></td>
